dashboard.generator

Class DatumGenerator

  • java.lang.Object
    • dashboard.generator.Generator
      • dashboard.generator.DatumGenerator

  • public class DatumGenerator
extends Generator
    Implements a Generator with a simple physics engine that simulates the ship's position and allows the user to control the ship. The physics engine is not meant to be an entirely accurate simulation of motion, rather one that is relatively simple to implement and still has good performance. In order to work, a DatumGenerator needs an ignition switch ToggleButton and a controller AuxArrowPad.
    Author:
    Mark Sabini

      • DatumGenerator

        public DatumGenerator(int interval)
        Creates a DatumGenerator with the specified timing interval. Note the interval refers to how often the DatumGenerator updates its Readouts - the internal physics engine uses its own timing interval.
        Parameters:
        interval - the time interval between updates, measured in milliseconds

      • generate

        public void generate()
        Updates all the Readouts associated with the DatumGenerator. A complete DatumGenerator setup will have one ToggleButton (ignition switch), one AuxArrowPad (controller), four LevelReadouts (two for engine control, two for speed), two SingleIncrementers (to control the engine levels), four BufferReadouts (to print out position and bearing), and several LocationUpdatables (such as a CompassReadout and MinimapReadout).
        Specified by:
        generate in class Generator
